cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper discusses the use of usage bibliometrics to measure research activity, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on scholarly publications and online access suggests cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as the most likely sub-category. The use of click-stream logs and download statistics also suggests relevance to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The discussion of different classes of readers and browsing behavior may also relate to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
